Bhakti, Harum Energy, United Tractors: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-04-28T01:59:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/bhakti-harum-energy-united-tractors-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 0.8 percent to 3,804.93.  PT Astra Otoparts (AUTO IJ): The producer of automotive and
motorcycle parts plans a five-for-one stock split, Kontan
reported, citing President Director Siswanto Prawiroatmodjo.
Astra Otoparts will also pay a dividend of 592 rupiah per share,
or a total of 456.5 billion rupiah ($53 million). The amount
represents 40 percent of Astra Otoparts’ 2010 net income, the
newspaper reported. The stock slid 0.6 percent to 16,750 rupiah.  PT Bhakti Investama (BHIT IJ): The  investment company  plans
to sell a 10 percent stake in PT MNC Sky Vision in its initial
public offering in the second half of this year, Investor Daily
Indonesia reported, without saying where it got the information.
Bhakti was unchanged at 167 rupiah.  PT Harum Energy (HRUM IJ): The coal producer will pay a
dividend of 659.1 billion rupiah, or 244 rupiah per share, in
June, Investor Daily reported, citing President Director Ray
Antonio Gunara. The amount represents 80 percent of Harum
Energy’s 2010 net income, the newspaper reported. The company
has allocated $30 million for capital expenditure this year, the
report said. Harum rose 0.5 percent to 9,400 rupiah.  PT United Tractors (UNTR IJ):  Indonesia ’s biggest heavy
equipment seller said first-quarter net income increased to 1.3
trillion rupiah from 907 billion rupiah a year earlier. United
Tractors rose 1.3 percent to 23,250 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  